Al-Jazeera verdicts: Twitter reaction
Three al-Jazeera reporters accused of supporting the banned Muslim Brotherhood have been jailed for seven years each in Egypt.Peter Greste, Mohammed Fahmy and Baher Mohamed were convicted by a court in Cairo of spreading false news and backing the Islamist group.The trio had denied the charges.Here is how the world reacted to the ruling - via tweets.